title: North Korean embassy reps arrive at Sepang police HQ
text:
SEPANG: Representatives from the North Korean embassy were seen at the Sepang district police headquarters on Saturday.
While hordes of media practitioners waited outside, a car bearing diplomatic plates were seen entering the compound of the headquarters at about 4.10pm Saturday.
They left about an hour later.
It is believed that North Korean that they were trying to gain access to their countryman, Ri Jong Chol, who was detained in Jalan Kuchai Lama on Friday night.
The 47-year-old Ri is the fourth suspect to be arrested over the assassination of Kim Jong-nam.
Jong-nam, the half-brother of North Korean leader Kim Jong-un, was allegedly killed by two women who splashed his face with a chemical at the KL International Airport 2 departure hall at about 9am on Monday. He was about to leave for Macau.
